Two common deployment techniques which can virtually eliminate downtime are :

1. Blue Green Deployment
In Blue Green Deployment, we serve the current app on one half of our environment (Blue)
while deploy our new application on the other half (Green)

2.Canary Deployment
In Canary Deployment we can switch the version of a small subset of servers or nodes first,
and gradually transform all others


Strangler Fig Pattern
Gradually replacing the components of a Legacy System into a Modern System instead of a risky Big Bang migration.
Legacy 100% Modern 0%
Legacy 75% Modern 25%
Legacy 50% Modern 50%
Legacy 25% Modern 75%
Legacy 0% Modern 100%